Package com.edatasource.receipts

Classes which define the exceptions thrown by the parsers.

See: Description

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    AddressParseException
    Exception which is thrown if the address is unable to be parsed.
    DocumentNavigatorException  
    DuplicateReceiptException
    Exception which is thrown when a receipt is considered a duplicate after parsing.
    EmptyReceiptListException  
    ParserException
    Base exception class for any errors that occur within the parsers.
    UnsupportedCurrencyException
    Exception thrown when a receipt has a currency which we are not currently supporting, like Yen, Euros, or funny money like Amazon Coins or Bitcoins.
    UnsupportedFormatException
    Exception which is thrown when a receipt is "recognized" by the parsing framework, but the parser purposefully is not handling the specific format.
    ValidationException
    Exception which is thrown when the receipt format no longer matches the expected type.
